RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) combines information retrieval with text generation.
It first searches a knowledge base for relevant documents, then uses those as context.
Benefits include reduced hallucinations and the ability to cite sources.
"""
rag.add_text(test_text, source="test.txt")

print("\n✅ Ready! Run rag.interactive() to start asking questions.")

